      "writtenOn": "2020-04-30T23:46:55Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e\u003e When runTestCmd returns a non-nil error, the exitCode is ignored.\n\nThat\u0027s what the below TODO at L94 is for.\n```\n// TODO(ddoman): tag the error with an exit code, and r.done() returns the exit code,\n// if tagged.\n```\n\nWe want rdb-stream to return the test programs\u0027 exit code, right? It implies that the user of rdb-stream wants to parse and recognize certains exit codes. If not, then rdb-stream wouldn\u0027t have to return the test program\u0027s exit code, but 1 or 0, like any other rdb-sub commands return.\n\nI think it\u0027s still valid for rdb-stream to return a special code, 1001, to indicate that the exit was due to an internal error. WDYT?",
