      "writtenOn": "2020-05-01T06:23:03Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m afraid that pbutil.CoereceToInvocationID() may look like a solution for general problems. I want the logic of cleaning the invocation ID to be used only for such an invocation ID generated for testing purposes.\n\nI cannot think of any real use cases that could utilize CoereceToInovcationID(). If a client somehow generated an invalid invocation ID, it should simply fail, and the code needs to be fixed to always generate a valid invocation ID.\n\nHow about moving cli.genInvID() into pbutil as following?\nIf it looks OK, then I will add it in a separate CL. It will require some unit tests to be added in pbutil.\n\n```\npackage pbutil\n\n// TestInvocationID creates and returns a test invocation ID is rare enough\n// to be unique globally.\n//\n// The ID is made of the current username and timestamp with random suffixes, so that it\u0027s\n// easy to find the creator and creation time for tracking purposes.\nfunc TestInvocationID():\n  .....\n```",
